There is about 80 columns. Only categorical columns contains null values. Let's check linear correlation betweens variables.¶

In [5]:

There is a lot of correlation between Overall Quality and SalePrice. Correlation is high on columns that contains Living Area and total numbers of rooms. We are going to drop this columns.¶

In [6]:

Now we need to check catoregical variables has influence to price and are they equal.¶

In [21]:
vizualize_catoregical_plot(train, 'SalePrice')

Values between groups are very close anyway there are some variables with different values. So all categorical data will be used. LinearRegression don't need data scaling. In this case it will be turn off. Rest of models need standarization.¶

In [22]:
seed =  random.seed(100) 
models = {
    'LR' : LinearRegression(normalize=True, n_jobs=-1),
    'Lasso' : Lasso(random_state=seed, alpha=0.1, normalize=True),
    'Ridge' : Ridge(random_state=seed, alpha=0.1, normalize=True),
    'Tree' : DecisionTreeRegressor(),
    'RF' : RandomForestRegressor(n_jobs=-1),
    'SVR' : SVR(),
    'KNN' : KNeighborsRegressor(n_jobs=-1)
}
results = pd.DataFrame(columns=['model'])
viz_df = pd.DataFrame(columns=['model', 'actual', 'predicted'])
for model_name in models:
    model = Pipeline(steps=[
            ('preprocessor', create_pipeline(cat_imputing_strategy='constant', num_imputing_strategy='mean',
                                             data=X_train, model_type = model_name)),
            ('classifier', models[model_name])
            ]
                    )
    
    clf = GridSearchCV(model, param_grid={}, cv=5, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error')
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    joblib.dump(clf,'models/'+model_name+'.sav')
    y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
    
    results = results.append(create_result_dataframe(y_test, y_pred, model_name))
    viz_df = viz_df.append(pd.DataFrame( 
                         {'actual': y_test, 
                         'predicted': y_pred, 
                         'model' : model_name}))
    
    plot_scatter_score(y_test, y_pred, model_name)
    visualize_score(viz_df[viz_df['model']==model_name], 25, name=model_name)
    print_score(y_test, y_pred)

Random Forest,¶
Support Vector Machine,¶
